<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 3:28PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Wake
and northeastern Chatham Counties through 430 PM EDT...
At 327 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pittsboro, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Raleigh, Cary, Pittsboro, Garner, Fuquay-Varina, RDU International,
Apex, Holly Springs, Morrisville and Lake Wheeler.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
